name: Address_Point
Description: A spatial data layer containing point geometry features for representing both the physical and mailing addresses for properties, buildings, and sub-address locations in Baltimore City, as documented in the City's real property and property location database sources. The data employs what's referred to as the City native schema/data standard, which has specific attribute field names, field formats, and data standards to support internal City services. The data contained in this data layer (number of features, accuracy, point locations) will match the data in the other address point data layer on Open Baltimore (“Address Point (NG911)”), just the format of the attribute field names and data standards will be different, as well as some internal City attributes fields have been added to support internal City services not related to a NG911 system. This data also employs the NAD 1983 StatePlane Maryland FIPS 1900 (US Feet) projected coordinate system (WKID: 2248). Data is updated on a quarterly basis.

name: Street_Centerline
Description: A spatial data layer containing line geometry features for representing the center line of roadways in Baltimore City, as documented in the City's enterprise GIS database and Department of Transportation right-of-way data sources. The data contains information on street address ranges, speed limits, one-way designations, street alias (a.k.a.) names, snow routes, and many other street related data. The data employs what's referred to as the City native schema/data standard, which has specific attribute field names, field formats, and data standards to support internal City services. The data contained in this data layer (number of features, accuracy, locations) will match the data in the other street centerline layer on Open Baltimore (“Street Centerline (NG911)”), just the format of the attribute field names and data standards will be different, as well as some internal City attributes fields have been added to support internal City services not related to a NG911 system. This data also employs the NAD 1983 StatePlane Maryland FIPS 1900 (US Feet) projected coordinate system (WKID: 2248). The data dictionary for this dataset can be accessed by visiting the following link.: Street Centerline (Native) Schema Data Dictionary | Open Baltimore (baltimorecity.gov). Data is updated on a quarterly basis.

name: Neighborhood_NSA
Description: These boundaries were developed by the Department of Planning based on 2020 Census data. Be aware that other organizations may use different neighborhood boundaries in their analyses.Demographics included are: race, ethnicity, gender, vacancy rate, homeowner status, family structure, and age.

name: bridge
Description: The data set locates bridges as a point feature class. The locations for bridges in the data set match the location maps provided with the bridge inspection reports. Attributes from the bridge inspection reports including 2006 Bridge Sufficiency Rating (BSR) and from SHA average daily traffic counts (ADT) were appended to the feature class. ADT dates are primarily from 2003.

name: MARC_Train
Description: This dataset represents the railroad line for the Maryland Area Regional Commuter (MARC) train system. Heavy Rail - Railroad centerlines for the City's Heavy rail system. Light Rail - Railroad centerlines for the City's Light rail system Subway Rail - Railroad centerlines for the City's subway system. Abandoned Rail - Railroad centerlines that are obviously abandoned as evidenced by vegetation overgrowth.
